features.title: Booking Protection Guarantee
features.subtitle: In the unlikely event a Host needs to cancel your booking within 30 days of check-in, we’ll find you a similar or better home, or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Check-In Guarantee
features.subtitle: If you can’t check into your home and the Host cannot resolve the issue, we’ll find you a similar or better home for the length of your original stay, or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Get-What-You-Booked Guarantee
features.subtitle: If at any time during your stay you find your listing isn't as advertised—for example, the refrigerator stops working and your Host can’t easily fix it, or it has fewer bedrooms than listed—you'll have three days to report it and we’ll find you a similar or better home, or we’ll refund you.

features.subtitle: If you ever feel unsafe, you’ll get priority access to specially-trained safety agents, day or night.

content.htmlText:
My house is situated on a quiet, suburban street removed from the hustle and bustle of the city. I think this best suits travelers who will want to see different parts of the city and have access to a car.

Mid-city isn't particularly a tourist destination itself and it’s not so walkable (as with most places in LA), but my homes is close to the 10 freeway which is the main highway through LA.

For travelers that want a taste of every part of LA from Downtown to Santa Monica, Hollywood, Koreatown, West Hollywood, Silver Lake etc it means you’ll usually be able to get wherever you want to go within 30 min even during rush hour.

As with most places in LA you'll occasionally hear airplanes overhead and helicopters whizzing around and also my neighbors enjoy setting off fireworks every now and then - especially around major holidays, so just a heads up.

section.houseRulesSubtitle: You'll be staying in someone's home, so please treat it with care and respect.

html.htmlText:
No parties, or guests over 3 people.

No smoking in the room. Any smoking will incur an additional $100 room cleaning fee.

The following rules regard the hot tub use:

> Do not eat or drink in the hot tub. Any contamination with food or drink will incur a $100 fee because the water will need to be drained and replaced.

> Shower before entering the hot tub to remove any makeup or oils that might contaminate the water.

> Do not wear any jewellery or items that could get caught in the hot tub jets. 

> If using the hot tub after 10pm please be respectful of the neighbours and do not make any disturbing noises or play music.

> You are using the hot tub at your own risk. By entering the hot tub you agree to abide by these rules. 

> Please replace the cover after you are finished to ensure the hot tub remains heated.

htmlDescription.htmlText:
Guest suite with separate entrance situated in Mid City. The room is not connected internally to the main house. Best suited for travelers looking for a central location to access the many different parts of LA either by car, ride share or metro. Only a 15 min walk to the Expo line. The best part is the patio and private/personal HOT TUB in the backyard to relax after a busy day exploring LA.

The space
The room features a queen bed, cosy private bathroom with shower and toilet and an epic backyard patio that is both peaceful and serene. The room features a reverse-cycle air conditioning, microwave, TV, coffee maker and clothes rack. The outdoor patio has a fireplace and the backyard has a hot tub with umbrella, picnic table as well as two sun chaises. Please note there are NO kitchen/cooking facilities. Think of it more like a hotel room. Also there is strictly NO smoking in the room. I think this Airbnb best suits guests who want a really central location and have a car to explore all the sights around LA. Or it suits guests who really love their outdoor space and really want a hot tub to relax in.

Guest access
There is free street parking.

During your stay
You’ll have tons of privacy. I’m usually always on site in case of problems and of course I’m happy to chat but I’m definitely more the kind of host that will leave you in peace.

Other things to note
My house is situated on a quiet, safe, suburban street removed from the hustle and bustle of the city. I think this best suits travellers who will want to see different parts of the city and have access to a car. Mid-city isn't particularly a tourist destination itself and it’s not so walkable (as with most places in LA), but my homes is close to the 10 freeway which is the main highway through LA. For travellers that want a taste of every part of LA from Downtown to Santa Monica, Hollywood, Koreatown, West Hollywood, Silver Lake etc it means you’ll usually be able to get wherever you want to go within 30 min even during rush hour. As with most places in LA you'll occasionally hear airplanes overhead and helicopters whizzing around and also my neighbors enjoy setting off fireworks every now and then - especially around major holidays, so just a heads up.
